#if($bullets.contains("childSafetyCTA"))
Keep children away from storm drains, culverts, creeks and streams. Water levels can rise rapidly and sweep children away.

#end
#if($bullets.contains("nighttimeCTA"))
Be especially cautious at night when it is harder to recognize the dangers of flooding. 

#end
#if($bullets.contains("urbanCTA"))
Excessive runoff from heavy rainfall will cause flooding of small creeks and streams, urban areas, highways, streets and underpasses as well as other drainage areas and low lying spots. 

#end
#if($bullets.contains("ruralCTA"))
Excessive runoff from heavy rainfall will cause flooding of small creeks and streams, country roads, farmland, and other low lying spots.

#end
#if($bullets.contains("stayAwayCTA"))
Stay away or be swept away. River banks and culverts can become unstable and unsafe. 

#end
#if($bullets.contains("lowSpotsCTA"))
In hilly terrain there are hundreds of low water crossings which are potentially dangerous in heavy rain. Do not attempt to cross flooded roads. Find an alternate route.

#end
